@startuml MultiServerIdempotentIssue

title Idempotent POST Issue - Multi-Server Case\nIndependent DBs + Slow Replication Cause Duplicate Processing

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam ArrowColor #555555
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam NoteBorderColor #F9A825
skinparam SequenceGroupBackgroundColor #F3F9FF
skinparam SequenceGroupBorderColor #4A90D9
skinparam SequenceBoxBackgroundColor #EEF7EE
skinparam SequenceBoxBorderColor #5A9E5A

autonumber

actor "Client" as client
participant "Load Balancer" as lb

box "Server Cluster" #EEF7EE
  participant "App Server 1" as s1
  participant "App Server 2" as s2
end box

box "Independent Databases" #F3F9FF
  database "DB 1\n(Server 1)" as db1
  database "DB 2\n(Server 2)" as db2
end box

== Problem Context ==
note over s1, db2
  Each application server writes to its own database.
  Database replication is asynchronous and can be delayed.
  If the retry lands on another server before replication completes,
  that server may not know the request was already processed.
end note

== Request #1 hits Server 1 ==
client -> lb : POST /orders\nIdempotency-Key: uuid-abc123\n(body: item=A, qty=1)
lb -> s1 : Route request to Server 1

s1 -> s1 : Validate Idempotency-Key header present
s1 -> db1 : CHECK idempotency_key = uuid-abc123
db1 --> s1 : NOT FOUND

s1 -> db1 : INSERT idempotency_key = uuid-abc123\nstatus = CREATED
s1 -> db1 : INSERT order\n(item=A, qty=1)
db1 --> s1 : OK (order_id=701)
s1 -> db1 : UPDATE idempotency_key\nstatus = CONSUMED\nresponse = {order_id:701}

note right of s1
  Server 1 has processed the request successfully.
  But only DB1 knows this right now.
end note

... network timeout / client did not receive response ...

== DB Replication is still pending ==
db1 ->> db2 : ASYNC REPLICATION\n(can lag seconds or minutes)

note over db1, db2 #F8CECC
  Replication has NOT completed yet.
  DB2 still does not have:
  - idempotency key uuid-abc123
  - order_id=701
end note

== Retry hits Server 2 ==
client -> lb : POST /orders\nIdempotency-Key: uuid-abc123\n(body: item=A, qty=1)
lb -> s2 : Route retry to Server 2

s2 -> s2 : Validate Idempotency-Key header present
s2 -> db2 : CHECK idempotency_key = uuid-abc123
db2 --> s2 : NOT FOUND

note right of s2 #F8CECC
  Server 2 incorrectly assumes this is a new request
  because DB2 has not received replication from DB1 yet.
end note

s2 -> db2 : INSERT idempotency_key = uuid-abc123\nstatus = CREATED
s2 -> db2 : INSERT order\n(item=A, qty=1)
db2 --> s2 : OK (order_id=702)
s2 -> db2 : UPDATE idempotency_key\nstatus = CONSUMED\nresponse = {order_id:702}
s2 -> client : HTTP 201 Created\n{order_id: 702}

== Duplicate Outcome ==
note over client, db2 #F8CECC
  ISSUE:
  Same logical request was processed twice.

  Server 1 created order_id=701 in DB1.
  Server 2 created order_id=702 in DB2.

  Root Cause:
  Idempotency state stored only in per-server DBs
  with slow asynchronous replication.
end note

@enduml

